helpdesk-ticket.subject: DNS / Hostmaster request
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello, I'm Matt, and I'm the chief engineer at WMSE Radio. I am seeking to request a DNS record. Currently, we have WMSE.ORG and WMSE.NET registered for the radio station website. Currently, both of these domain names point to DNS1.MSOE.EDU and DNS2.MSOE.EDU which is great as it makes MSOE the primary DNS record for our domains. I am writing to request the addition of two A records under WMSE.NET. Would you please add the following to our DNS record? A TECH.WMSE.NET 98.103.128.98 A STREAM.WMSE.NET 98.103.128.99 These IP addresses belong to the static IP's of our Time Warner business class internet we have installed at Krueger Hall. "TECH" will be used to access ourTransmitter and Emergency Alert System for 24/7 engineering response. "STREAM" will be used for web streaming and remote codec uplinks. If you have any further questions, please don't hesitate to write or call. Thanks for your time and assistance! -MattRock

I am writing to request the addition of two A records under WMSE.NET.  Would you please add the following to our DNS record?

  • A  TECH.WMSE.NET      98.103.128.98
  • A  STREAM.WMSE.NET  98.103.128.99

These IP addresses belong to the static IP's of our Time Warner business class internet we have installed at Krueger Hall. "TECH" will be used to access ourTransmitter and Emergency Alert System for 24/7 engineering response.  "STREAM" will be used for web streaming and remote codec uplinks.

If you have any further questions, please don't hesitate to write or call.  Thanks for your time and assistance!

-MattRock

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Matt Rockwell,
Will these need to be available both internally and externally to users? We maintain both an internal DNS (only viewable by users on an MSOE IP address range) and external DNS (viewable by anyone). Once I know if you need one or both, it's only a small change to make this live.
Thanks

helpdesk-note.body:
I set the anayslmd.lic file and the proper servers in the license manager utility, however, it still seemed to not work. I noted that this is not for ansys notebench but rather is for designer for the electromagnetic ansys suite.
After talking with Mike I'm moving this ticket over to the system administrator team so they can take a look at how the licenses for this suite need to be set up client side.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
I set the anayslmd.lic file and the proper servers in the license manager utility, however, it still seemed to not work. I noted that this is not for ansys notebench but rather is for designer for the electromagnetic ansys suite.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: My wireless mouse disconnects often. I start to log in each morning and then have to shut down because I can't connect to OUTLOOK.
helpdesk-ticket.description: Logging into OUTLOOK and wireless mouse quits on me at least 4-5 times a day.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Logging into OUTLOOK and wireless mouse quits on me at least 4-5 times a day.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi piaskosk, For your wireless mouse, probably the batteries in the mouse need to be replaced. Or maybe the mouse itself has gone bad?
For your Outlook to work on your laptop, you can follow these steps-
1. Open Start Menu, and search for “Credential Manager”. 2. Open Credential Manager. 3. You should see an option saying “Generic Credentials” 4. Under generic credentials, there should be a an option saying “MSOutlook15…” 5. Click on that and press “Remove from Vault” and say Yes to the prompt. 6. Close credential manger and re-open outlook. 7. Outlook will ask you for your new password and will start updating.
Let us know if we can assist you with anything else.
Thanks
Rishabh Gupta
Help Desk Technician
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2433 Logging into OUTLOOK and wireless mouse quits on me at least 4-5 times a day.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi piaskosk,

For your wireless mouse, probably the batteries in the mouse need to be replaced. Or maybe the mouse itself has gone bad?

For your Outlook to work on your laptop, you can follow these steps-

1. Open Start Menu, and search for “Credential Manager”.
2. Open Credential Manager.
3. You should see an option saying “Generic Credentials”
4. Under generic credentials, there should be a an option saying “MSOutlook15…”
5. Click on that and press “Remove from Vault” and say Yes to the prompt.
6. Close credential manger and re-open outlook.
7. Outlook will ask you for your new password and will start updating.

We'd like to change our candidate application from a word document to a writeable PDF. From some cursory Googling, it looks like you have to have a certain specific version of Adobe in order to do so. I'm assuming that we as an institution have this version, somewhere, but I'm wondering if only certain people have access to it. Or, if we don't actually have it. Could someone provide some insight? Whether we have it or not, and if we don't, what we might need to do to get it?
Your help is much appreciated.
Thank you,
Elise

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Elise Grinbergs, MSOE does not have Adobe Acrobat Pro. It is something you'd need to purchase as a department, or individually. If memory serves, it stands at slightly under $100 per machine Adobe Acrobat Pro would be installed on. As a department, I believe it can be requisitioned if requested. In summary, we do not have Adobe Acrobat Pro to give you access to. However, if you do obtain it, we would be more than happy to assist you in setting it up if you do purchase it. Thank You,
Bryan Voss Tier 1 Technician

In summary, we do not have Adobe Acrobat Pro to give you access to. However, if you do obtain it, we would be more than happy to assist you in setting it up if you do purchase it.

Hi Aimee,
I apologize for the confusion we will not be able to provide M drive access for you. The M drive is used for student work such as senior design projects. The best solution for would be to store your documents on Box. Using Box will allow you to share your files with your students workers and access them from any computer you log into. Here are a couple links that will help you get started uploading your files to Box. Let us know if you have any questions.
Logging into Box https://community.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3253
Navigating Boxes website https://community.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3261

helpdesk-note.body: I went over and looked at this thing. It appears one of the drives is having issues and the raid is in verify state. Suposedly this causes the computer to stop booting windows at the splash screen and do a full verify before booting into windows. We are giving it a few hours to hopefully remedy itself before we do anything else.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Elizabeth,
MSOE has a system set up so students can download software from our network under Get Programs. We also have guides in place to walk students through this process. Moreover our guides walk students through the process of allowing the installation process to automatically pull a license file for you off of the MSOE network. Manually placing a license key into the license folder under ansys wont work. Here is how we can fix the problem: 1) If you have any form of ansys Electromagnet currently on your computer, uninstall by going to Start<Control Panel<Programs<Uninstall a Program 2) Restart your computer 3) Follow the guide I have attached in this email.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT - Assistant Systems Administrator

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi andersonm,
Have you recently changed your password? This may be causing a problem with Outlook updating properly. Webmail will always have the most recent update to your mailbox as long as you are signed in properly because it is managed online by Microsoft. Outlook is not managed directly by Microsoft. It simply pulls from Webmail whenever the correct credentials are entered.
The way that Outlook interacts with MSOE's Single Sign On can occasionally cause problems. If you check the "Remember Me" box when you log in to Outlook, Outlook will store the credentials you entered at that time in a program called Credential Manager, and it uses these to log in. These saved credentials are not touched when you change your MSOE password, so Outlook would be pulling your old credentials from the Credential Manager, which logs you successfully into Outlook, but not your actual email account, so it will not update.
This can be easily fixed by deleting the old credential entry, which will force Outlook to ask you for your most recent credentials.
1. Open the Start menu and type "Credential Manager" into the search bar. Click on the application when it appears in the list.
2. When the Credential Manager window opens, there should be a label that reads "Generic Credentials". Under this label should be an entry that reads something along the lines of "MS.Outlook.youremailaddress". Click on this entry and choose the option "Remove from Vault". A warning message will appear. Click "Yes".
3. Close the Credential Manager and close Outlook if it is not already closed. When you open Outlook again, it should prompt you for your password. Feel free to check "Remember Me" again, just be aware that you will have to delete from the Credential Manager again the next time you change your password. Once you are successfully logged in, Outlook should begin updating correctly.
Please let me know if this solves your issue. Have a great day! Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2501

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Extent of IT Support for Students
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi Helpdesk staff,
I have several students in my courses who are having problems with MATLAB installations on their MSOE laptops. They have told me that they have visited IT numerous times in attempts to get these issues resolved, but that IT will only wipe the machine clean, reinstall the OS, join it to the domain, and send them on their way.
Is software support truly out of scope under the recent changes to the structure of the IT department? If so, who can I speak with about this decision?
Thanks for your time,
Prof. Paul Gessler Adjunct Lecturer Mechanical Engineering Department Milwaukee School of Engineering
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

They have told me that they have visited IT numerous times in attempts to get these issues resolved, but that IT will only wipe the machine clean, reinstall the OS, join it to the domain, and send them on their way.
 
Is software support truly out of scope under the recent changes to the structure of the IT department? If so, who can I speak with about this decision?
 
Thanks for your time,
 
Prof. Paul Gessler
Adjunct Lecturer
Mechanical Engineering Department
Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Paul Gessler, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2513
Our standard procedure is not to wipe a machine, but to troubleshoot the issue. If basic software troubleshooting fails, we will reinstall the software. Re-imaging a machine is always a last resort unless specifically requested by the useer. I will be closing this ticket, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

StudentAccounts-Staff@msoe.edu, TRIO-Staff@msoe.edu, mathematics-staff@msoe.edu, PLTW-Staff@msoe.edu

How to Fix It
Ask the owner of the group to grant you permission to send to the group, and then try to send a message again. If the group belongs to a different organization than yours, contact the organization's customer service department for assistance. If the group is in your organization and you don't know who the group owner is, you can find it by doing the following in either Outlook on the web or Outlook:
  • Open your Sent folder, and then select the original message.
  • If you're using Outlook on the web, select the group name located on the To or CC line. If you're using Outlook, double-click the group name on the To or CC line.
  • In Outlook on the web, from the pop-up dialog box, choose Owner. In Outlook, choose Contact. The owner's name is listed under Owner.
The owner of the group may have intentionally chosen to restrict who can send messages to it, and they may not want to adjust the existing restriction. In this case, you'll have to contact the group members by some other means, such as sending an email message to their individual email addresses or contacting them by phone.

More Info for Email Admins

This error occurs when the owner of the distribution group or security group has set up the group to accept messages only from certain addresses. Even a group owner may not be automatically granted permission to send messages to the group.

To fix this issue, the group owner must add the sender's address to the group's allowed senders list. Usually this issue can only be fixed by the group owner.

For more information and steps to fix this issue, see Fix email delivery issues for error code 5.7.124 in Office 365.

Your message couldn't be delivered to multiple groups.
The groups at msoe.edu only accept messages from people on their allowed senders list, and your email address isn't on the lists.
helpdesk Office 365 Multiple groups
Sender Action Required
Sender not allowed
Couldn't deliver to the following groups:
StudentAccounts-Staff@msoe.edu, TRIO-Staff@msoe.edu, mathematics-staff@msoe.edu, PLTW-Staff@msoe.edu

How to Fix It
Ask the owner of the group to grant you permission to send to the group, and then try to send a message again. If the group belongs to a different organization than yours, contact the organization's customer service department for assistance. If the group is in your organization and you don't know who the group owner is, you can find it by doing the following in either Outlook on the web or Outlook:
  • Open your Sent folder, and then select the original message.
  • If you're using Outlook on the web, select the group name located on the To or CC line. If you're using Outlook, double-click the group name on the To or CC line.
  • In Outlook on the web, from the pop-up dialog box, choose Owner. In Outlook, choose Contact. The owner's name is listed under Owner.
The owner of the group may have intentionally chosen to restrict who can send messages to it, and they may not want to adjust the existing restriction. In this case, you'll have to contact the group members by some other means, such as sending an email message to their individual email addresses or contacting them by phone.

Was this helpful? Send feedback to Microsoft.

More Info for Email Admins
Status code: 550 5.7.124

This error occurs when the owner of the distribution group or security group has set up the group to accept messages only from certain addresses. Even a group owner may not be automatically granted permission to send messages to the group.

To fix this issue, the group owner must add the sender's address to the group's allowed senders list. Usually this issue can only be fixed by the group owner.

For more information and steps to fix this issue, see Fix email delivery issues for error code 5.7.124 in Office 365.

helpdesk-note.body: I called Dr. Williams and discussed the issue he was seeing with search not appearing. I was not able to recreate the issue and he isn't observing it any more. I am going to flag this issue as a potential defect that we can try forcing in the UAT development environment. helpdesk-ticket.subject: Survey Links
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good Morning,
Our office is currently gathering graduates' and student's information through our Graduate Survey and Internship Survey. After the www.msoe.edu<http://www.msoe.edu> update, I double-checked the two survey links this morning, and they do work in Google Chrome and Firefox browsers. However, the links don't work in Internet Explorer. Here are the URLs the links go to in IE:
Graduate Survey (www.msoe.edu/graduate-survey<http://www.msoe.edu/graduate-survey>) goes to this URL in IE: http://www.msoe.edu/academics/mathematics-undergraduate/ Internship Survey (www.msoe.edu/internship-survey<http://www.msoe.edu/internship-survey>) goes to this URL in IE: http://www.msoe.edu/academics/labs/
The shortened URL for the Graduate Survey should take the user here: http://www.msoe.edu/explore-your-future/career-services/graduate-employment-survey/
If there's anything we can do to help with the process, please let me know!
Thank you,
Jennifer Abing Assistant Director of Career Services Milwaukee School of Engineering (MSOE) (414) 277-7119 abing@msoe.edu<mailto:abing@msoe.edu> www.msoe.edu/career_services<http://www.msoe.edu/career_services> Follow Career Services<http://www.msoe.edu/community/explore-your-future/career-services/career-services-department> on the HUB! Pronouns: she/her
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Good Morning,
 
Our office is currently gathering graduates’ and student’s information through our Graduate Survey and Internship Survey.  After the www.msoe.edu update, I double-checked the two survey links this morning, and they do work in Google Chrome and Firefox browsers.  However, the links don’t work in Internet Explorer.  Here are the URLs the links go to in IE:
 
Graduate Survey (www.msoe.edu/graduate-survey) goes to this URL in IE:  http://www.msoe.edu/academics/mathematics-undergraduate/
Internship Survey (www.msoe.edu/internship-survey) goes to this URL in IE:  http://www.msoe.edu/academics/labs/
 
The shortened URL for the Graduate Survey should take the user here:  http://www.msoe.edu/explore-your-future/career-services/graduate-employment-survey/
 
If there’s anything we can do to help with the process, please let me know!
 
Thank you,
 
Jennifer Abing
Assistant Director of Career Services
Milwaukee School of Engineering (MSOE)
(414) 277-7119
abing@msoe.edu
www.msoe.edu/career_services

Or, it could be a fluke with the website maintenance, and the problem has been corrected.
If this continues to be an issue with your computer, we can continue troubleshooting.

helpdesk-note.body:
Nathan,
If you are getting that IP address, then you have access to DNS. The same appliance handles both DHCP and DNS. You may wish to do an ipconfig/flushdns or reboot, or check to be certain that you have your IPv4 properties set to automatically choose a DNS, or that it's set to the following:
primary 155.92.194.41 secondary 205.217.190.31
Failing that, you can use Google as your DNS. I do here at work so I can tell when our local changes have propagated outside the environment.
I'm fairly sure you will find a settings issue in IPv4. We tested the port when we corrected the issue and verified full connectivity on the test laptop.
Keep us posted
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2574 The Wired Network Connection in My apartment is not working, specifically the direct connection does not host a DHCP connection, it also does not allow direct IP access outside of the schools network. Follows are the results of some basic troubleshooting steps.
Windows 10 PC connected directly to the wall ping 8.8.8.8 Timeout ping 155.92.5.80 Success ping google.com Timeout ping emerald.msoe.edu Success
IT personell have my permission to enter my room ( 1208 ) Affected port is 08-A
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Nathan,

If you are getting that IP address, then you have access to DNS. The same appliance handles both DHCP and DNS. You may wish to do an ipconfig/flushdns or reboot, or check to be certain that you have your IPv4 properties set to automatically choose a DNS, or that it's set to the following:

primary 155.92.194.41
secondary 205.217.190.31

Failing that, you can use Google as your DNS. I do here at work so I can tell when our local changes have propagated outside the environment.

I'm fairly sure you will find a settings issue in IPv4. We tested the port when we corrected the issue and verified full connectivity on the test laptop.

Keep us posted

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi urbain, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/2589
Thank you for bringing this to our attention. We will take a look at the signal strength in the area and determine if it is necessary to install another access point to provide better quality of service in the area.
I would suggest that you make sure that you are connected to the "MSOE" network or the "MSOE internal" network. These two networks have a greater priority than the "MSOE guest" network and tend to have higher average speeds.
Have a nice day
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: here is a plot of signal strength at the location. Most channels are pushing around -70dB. That should be around 50-60% signal strength on most devices
helpdesk-note.body-html: here is a plot of signal strength at the location. Most channels are pushing around -70dB. That should be around 50-60% signal strength on most devices

helpdesk-note.body: The problem is that MSOE is broadcasting on all channels. APs are either set too high with regards to power, are too close together, or are hopping channels in competition with each other. This is probably a config issue, and adding an AP will likely make the issue worse, not better. I'll have Jason take a look.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Bill,
I'm sorry to hear that your computer is running slow. It can be difficult for us in IT to know exactly what is wrong when all the information we have is "computer is slow, freezing, etc."
There are many causes for why a computer is running slow. I took the liberty to find this article on Microsoft's website detailing how to optimize windows 7 performance. I looked through the list and it was quite accurate. Please try these steps and let us know if the problem still persists.
Adding RAM to your computer will definitely allow you to run more programs at the same time, but it will not solve all issues. It is best to have a conversation about your need for more RAM with your the department chair, as they will need to find the funding for that extra RAM. IT does not have unused RAM to disperse.
Please let us know if the problem persists. I strongly believe if you follow that guide you will notice a huge improvement in your performance.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Please assign the ticket to the MSOE Community Team, and specifically to Chaning Ogden.
Thank you.
From: Sarah Gelhaar [mailto:gelha017@umn.edu] Sent: Friday, November 06, 2015 11:39 AM To: Hub Subject: confirmation email difficulty
Hello,
I Spoke with MSOE's IT department and the registrar department, and as a conclusion they asked me to send an email here describing my issue. I have been in contact with people in your admissions office because I am trying to apply to the accelerated nursing program. In order to be accepted there I need to take a prerequisite class that they would like me to start on November 30th. In order to determine which class or classes I need to take starting at the end of the month I need to do a transfer application so that they can look at my transcripts from other universities. So, on MSOE's website, in order to get to the application I first have to make a community account. I made a community account with this email and a password. It approved everything and told me that I had "one more step" and needed to confirm the email via a link in an email they would send me to this address. However, I have not received a confirmation email. I have waited a few hours, and I have tried going through the process twice. When I went through the process a second time, it did not flag the email as already being in use, and allowed me to proceed. However, the second time I still didn't get a confirmation email. I have also tried just signing into the MSOE account, and it says it does not recognize my email address. I have checked my spam box as well, and nothing has appeared. Nobody that I have spoken to on the phone seems to know how to fix this problem, so I am hoping you can help. I am in a bit of a time crunch because they want me to start at the end of the month, and I still need to get my application in and transcripts sent over, which we know also takes time. Thank you for any help you can provide!
Sincerely, Sarah Gelhaar

Thank you.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Hub pages creating links for phone numbers
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I am browsing the hub using Microsoft Edge, the standard browser with Windows 10. In each case, when there is a phone number, clicking on it opens a blank window with no content. Note the screen capture below. Each of the phone numbers has a hyperlink associated with it. This is not a problem with chrome, so there must be something in the css style sheet that is causing edge to think that these are links.
[cid:image001.png@01D118CF.737B4390]
Dr. Walter Schilling Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering EECS Department schilling@msoe.edu<mailto:schilling@msoe.edu>
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I am browsing the hub using Microsoft Edge, the standard browser with Windows 10.  In each case, when there is a phone number, clicking on it opens a blank window with no content.  Note the screen capture below.  Each of the phone numbers has a hyperlink associated with it.  This is not a problem with chrome, so there must be something in the css style sheet that is causing edge to think that these are links.
 
 
 
 
Dr. Walter Schilling
Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering
EECS Department
schilling@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Schilling,
Sorry for any confusion the varied formatting might have created. Based on the supported browser functionality, the link formatting is based on the "tel" URI scheme. This can be further explained at the Microsoft Developer portal (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn265018(v=vs.85).aspx).
Given the potential usefulness of this behavior, we will consider disallowing the formatting of phone numbers in future designs. Should there be any further questions or concerns, I would love to further discuss them.
Does this address your concern regarding the phone number formatting?
Regards,

I was issued my new laptop on September 1st, 2015 just before I left for Germany. I did not realize until now but my laptop does not have Global Protect installed and I cannot connect to the school network. Is there any way I can get global connect, or is there another way to connect to the network?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

I am a Junior in the Mechanical engineering program, I am currently spending the 2015-2016 school year studying abroad in Germany. I was issued my new laptop on September 1st, 2015 just before I left for Germany. I did not realize until now but my laptop does not have Global Protect installed and I cannot connect to the school network. Is there any way I can get global connect, or is there another way to connect to the network?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi,
You can install Global Protect by going to https://sslvpn.msoe.edu. When you sign in with your username and password, you can install the 64bit version of global protect. Let us know if this works out. If you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Sincerely, Nathan Stachowiak

helpdesk-ticket.subject: MSOE Community Not expiring credentials properly
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I am working with the MSOE community. For some reason, it is allowing me to log onto the community using credentials which are expired / have not been recently entered. This seems to be a weakness in the SSO functionality in that it is allowing me to enter into the system using old credentials. See the video captured here.
Dr. Walter Schilling Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering EECS Department schilling@msoe.edu<mailto:schilling@msoe.edu>
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I am working with the MSOE community.  For some reason, it is allowing me to log onto the community using credentials which are expired / have not been recently entered.  This seems to be a weakness in the SSO functionality in that it is allowing me to enter into the system using old credentials.  See the video captured here.
 
 
 
 
Dr. Walter Schilling
Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering
EECS Department
schilling@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: Sent to MSOE Community Team.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Sent to MSOE Community Team.

helpdesk-note.body:
Michael,
Any ideas as to why the SSO authentication wouldn't identify expired credentials?
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Michael,

Any ideas as to why the SSO authentication wouldn't identify expired credentials?

helpdesk-note.body: He either has another instance of Chrome open or it is running in the background. To stop it from running in the background goto setting -> Show Advanced Setting - and uncheck the box under System called Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed..
helpdesk-note.body-html: He either has another instance of Chrome open or it is running in the background.  To stop it from running in the background goto setting -> Show Advanced Setting - and uncheck the box under System called Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed..

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Schilling,
I can see where that would be of concern. I was wondering if you by chance have the option for "Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed" enabled? It is found under Settings > Advanced Settings > System. I noticed a similar behavior when this was enabled.
Please let me know if this does not immediately address the issue you are observing.
Regards,

helpdesk-note.body:
I just tried unclicking that. No change when I run in incognito mode. I am never being asked to enter my password.
Not knowing exactly how authentication is being handled, but it seems to me that log out is not properly invalidating the cookie that is storing the session information and / or logout is not deleting the authentication token.
Walt

helpdesk-note.body: I can't recreate this. Have any users reported this type of behavior before? Do we know how long our timeout is for sessions?
helpdesk-note.body-html: I can't recreate this. Have any users reported this type of behavior before? Do we know how long our timeout is for sessions?

helpdesk-note.body: I was able to recreate after signing into Chrome. It adds a background App into your taskbar. Sessions stay active for 8 hours. No others users have reported this type of behavior.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I was able to recreate after signing into Chrome.  It adds a background App into your taskbar.  Sessions stay active for 8 hours.  No others users have reported this type of behavior.

helpdesk-note.body:
I saw the same and was able to do the same, but based on his response, he has the same behavior with background apps disable and when in incognito mode. If that is the case, it seems it would be more configuration related, but I can't reproduce his issue.
Would you be willing to respond to him explaining the configuration for SSO that addresses his concern of sessions not expiring? The fact we don't see this for multiple users makes me feel he is doing something and not fully explaining his process.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Schilling,
I am still trying to reproduce your issue. So far when Chrome is running int he background and I log into community.msoe.edu then logout and close my browser, I am able to reopen Chrome and not have to enter my credentials when I goto login.
When Chrome is not running in the background and I logout and close the browser. When I reopen Chrome I am required to enter my credentials.
When I run in incognito mode I required to re-enter my credentials after closing my browser regardless if Chrome is running in the background or not.
Anything else you can think of that would cause your Chrome configuration to be different? Do you have another SSO application running such as blackboard or Email that msoe.edu could be using the session token to sign in?

helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Schilling,
We are marking this issue as resolved as we had several people test this in different environments with different levels of access and could not recreate the issue. We asked for any details we may have missed, and didn't hear back after six days. The tickets are meant to auto-resolved after two days without a response, but the feature was not working as intended.
Marking resolved.
